  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "21. Suppose \"there is a man,\" &c.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "equity—rather \"with success,\" as the Hebrew is rendered (Ec 11:6), \"prosper,\" though Margin gives \"right\" [Holden and Maurer].",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "evil—not in itself, for this is the ordinary course of things, but \"evil,\" as regards the chief good, that one should have toiled so fruitlessly.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
